nodes.text: Walker Luskeske was a Human male who lived on Naboo during the Galactic Civil War. By the time of the Battle of Yavin, he served as security officer at Stonewall Labs, along with Kippy Martin, under the orders of the Security Chief Vance Groten. After he retired, Luskeske resided at Dee'ja Peak. He was also a hunter. Circa 1 ABY, Walker Luskeske asked a spacer to kill mountain spineflaps, including Sprywing, and narglatches in the Gallo Mountains and bring him wings, talons and fangs as trophies. In exchange, he gave the spacer a security beacon from Stonewall Labs.

Walker Luskeske appeared as a non-player character in the 2003 video game Star Wars Galaxies, a massively multiplayer online role-playing game developed by Sony Online Entertainment and published by LucasArts, prior to its closure on December 15, 2011. Walker Luskeske was added to the game as part of the "Legacy Quest" with the release of the "Publish 25", a.k.a. the "New Game Enhancements", on November 15, 2005.
"Walker Luskeske" is a clear wordplay of "Luke Skywalker."
